title: Peanut Butter Chocolate Bars
ingredients:1 cup crunchy peanut butter//
3/4 cup packed brown sugar//
3/4 cup light corn syrup//
1 teaspoon vanilla//
5 cups Rice Crispy cereal//
2 cups semi sweet chocolate chips
instructions:Heat oven to 275F.//
Grease 13x9x2 inch pan.//
In a heavy 3 quart saucepan, combine peanut butter, brown sugar, and corn syrup.//
Heat over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves, about 3 minutes.//
Do not boil, stir in vanilla.//
Gently fold in cereal until completely coated.//
Spread in pan and press firmly.//
Immediately sprinkle on chocolate chips.//
Place pan in oven to melt chips 2 to 3 minutes.//
Spread melted chips evenly over bars.//
Cool to set chocolate.